Description: CVE-2026-28693 - Add overflow checks to BMP/DIB write paths and DIB read path
 ImageMagick prior to 6.9.13-41 has integer overflow vulnerabilities in the
 DIB coder read and write paths, and the BMP coder write path, that can result
 in out-of-bounds read or write when processing malformed DIB/BMP images.
 This patch adds overflow checks using HeapOverflowSanityCheckGetSize before
 unsafe multiplications in bytes_per_line and length calculations.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/c54e9b365118972f939b0efcdd5087e106eb8945
Bug: https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/pull/8573
Author: ImageMagick Team
Last-Update: 2026-03-11

