Description: CVE-2026-30883 - Fix heap overflow in PNG raw profile writing
 An extremely large image profile could result in a heap overflow (heap
 over-write) when encoding a PNG image. The vulnerability is in the
 Magick_png_write_raw_profile() function in coders/png.c, where an
 insufficient bounds check on the length parameter allows integer overflow
 leading to undersized allocation and subsequent heap corruption.
 This patch adds an additional check to ensure the length does not exceed
 PNG_UINT_31_MAX / 2, preventing the integer overflow.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/3875619331d2c7c74a80d34665cbc06e6ed4359a
Author: Dirk Lemstra <dirk@lemstra.org>
Last-Update: 2026-03-11

--- a/coders/png.c
+++ b/coders/png.c
@@ -7978,7 +7978,7 @@
    description_length=(png_uint_32) strlen((const char *) profile_description);
    allocated_length=(png_uint_32) (2*length+(length >> 5)+description_length+
      20);
-   if (allocated_length < length)
+   if ((allocated_length < length) || (length >= (PNG_UINT_31_MAX / 2)))
      {
        (void) ThrowMagickException(exception,GetMagickModule(),CoderError,
          "maximum profile length exceeded","`%s'",image_info->filename);
