Description: CVE-2026-25985 - Fix excessive memory allocation in SVG processing
 A crafted SVG file can trigger excessive memory allocation (~674 GB),
 resulting in denial of service through out-of-memory conditions.
 Moved allocation to fix possible memory leak when at recursion depth.
 Backported from ImageMagick 7.x commit 1a51eb9.
 .
 Changes:
 1. CheckPrimitiveExtent: Add GetMaxMemoryRequest() and IsNaN() bounds check
    before attempting reallocation, preventing excessively large extent values.
 2. TraceBezier: Replace MAGICK_SSIZE_MAX with GetMaxMemoryRequest() for
    tighter bounds on coordinate distance checks.
 3. TraceBezier: Move the allocation size validation to after quantum is
    computed (quantum=MagickMin), checking against GetMaxMemoryRequest()
    instead of checking each y-alpha individually against MAGICK_SSIZE_MAX.
    This prevents excessive memory allocation by validating the final
    computed quantum before the points allocation.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick/commit/1a51eb9af00c36724660e294520878fd1f13e312
