Description: CVE-2026-28690 - Fix stack buffer overflow in MNG encoder
 A stack buffer overflow vulnerability exists in ImageMagick's MNG encoder
 (coders/png.c). A missing bounds check allows attacker-controlled data to
 corrupt the stack when processing a specially crafted image with PseudoClass
 storage and more than 256 colors, potentially leading to denial of service
 or code execution. This patch adds NULL checks on ImageToBlob return values
 and validates storage class before MNG encoding.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/6a602fb36f181a0089848344a3b0d79fc6155a2b
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-03-11

