Description: CVE-2026-26284 - PCD Huffman decoding initialization fix
 The DecodeImage function in coders/pcd.c contains an incorrect loop
 initialization (starting at index 0 instead of 1) when decoding Huffman
 table entries. This triggers a heap-buffer-overflow (out-of-bounds read)
 because the first entry at index 0 is a sentinel/header and not a valid
 table entry. Change the loop init from i=0 to i=1 to prevent the OOB read.
