Description: CVE-2026-25971 - Add thread-aware recursion detection in MSL coder
 ImageMagick fails to check for circular references between MSL
 (Magick Scripting Language) files, which can trigger a stack overflow
 via uncontrolled recursion. The recursive call chain is:
 MSLStartElement -> ReadImage -> ReadMSLImage -> ProcessMSLScript ->
 xmlParseChunk -> MSLStartElement. This patch adds splay-tree-based
 recursion detection keyed by thread ID to prevent infinite recursion
 when processing MSL files that reference each other.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/74e89a3dad41f89dfa74399c0b087d3ee4e81f90
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-02-24
Generated from Debian Bullseye source (deb11u10) + upstream fix logic.

