Description: CVE-2026-28692 - Fix heap over-read in MAT image coder
 ImageMagick prior to 6.9.13-41 has a heap over-read vulnerability in the
 MAT decoder (coders/mat.c) caused by 32-bit integer overflow. The
 multiplication of MATLAB_HDR.SizeX by constants (2, 4, or 8) was performed
 using 32-bit unsigned arithmetic before being cast to ssize_t, causing
 overflow with large SizeX values. This patch relocates the (ssize_t) cast
 to apply before the multiplication, and fixes a related truncation in the
 size validation check.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/ImageMagick/ImageMagick6/commit/6a602fb36f181a0089848344a3b0d79fc6155a2b
Author: Cristy <urban-warrior@imagemagick.org>
Last-Update: 2026-02-22
---

