Description: CVE-2026-30936 - Fix heap overflow in WaveletDenoiseImage
 A crafted image could cause an out-of-bounds heap write inside the
 WaveletDenoiseImage method when processing images with the
 -wavelet-denoise operation. The hardcoded 5 wavelet decomposition
 levels caused buffer overflow on images smaller than 32 pixels in
 either dimension. This patch adds dynamic bounds checking to
 number_levels to prevent the overflow.
Origin: upstream, commit:ffbbd7201e0ba08707849c0053aa703e076bf86e
Author: ImageMagick Authors
Last-Update: 2026-03-11
